23class __FCOther : public __FCBaseData {
24public:
27 void SetCmperAndInci(CMPER cmper, twobyte inci)
28 {
29 _dataid.other.cmper = cmper;
30 _dataid.other.inci = inci;
31 }
32
33
34public:
35 const char* ClassName() override { return "__FCOther"; }
36
38 __FCOther() : __FCBaseData() {}
39
40
47 bool IsIdenticalRecord(__FCOther* pCompare)
48 {
49 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return false;
50 if (_dataid.other.cmper != pCompare->_GetDataID()->other.cmper) return false;
51 if (_dataid.other.inci != pCompare->_GetDataID()->other.inci) return false;
52 return true;
53 }
54};

156class FCOtherInci : public __FCInciOther
157{
158 twobyte _inciblock[6];
159
160 int DataSizeLoad() override { return sizeof(_inciblock); } /* A standard inci */
161 void* Allocate() override { return _GetDataPtr(); }
162 EXTAG Tag() override { return GetCustomTag(); }
163
168 void CloneMemoryFrom(__FCBaseData* pSource) override
169 {
170 memcpy(&_inciblock, ((FCOtherInci*)pSource)->_GetDataPtr(), sizeof(_inciblock));
171 _datablock = &_inciblock;
172 _loadedsize = sizeof(_inciblock);
173 }
174
175 __FCBaseData* CreateObject() override
176 {
177 return new FCOtherInci();
178 }
179public:
180
181 FCOtherInci() : __FCInciOther()
182 {
183 memset(&_inciblock, 0, sizeof(_inciblock));
184 _datablock = &_inciblock;
185 _loadedsize = sizeof(_inciblock);
186 }
187
188#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
195 void* _GetDataPtr() { return &_inciblock; }
196#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
197
198 const char* ClassName() override { return "FCOtherInci"; }
199 const PDKFRAMEWORK_CLASSID GetClassID() const override { return FCID_OTHERINCI; }
200};

488#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_COMPOSITETIMESIGS
497class FCCompositeTimeSigTop : public __FCCollectionInciOther
498{
500 ECompositeTimeUpper* _pArray;
501
504 int _arraycounter;
505
506#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
511 ECompositeTimeUpper* _GetGroupElementPtr(int groupindex, int subindex)
512 {
513 groupindex++; /* Make the index 1-based internally for this method */
514 int currentindex = 0;
515 int subindexcount = 0;
516 for (int i = 0; i < _arraycounter; i++)
517 {
518 if (_pArray[i].chainstart) currentindex++;
519 if (currentindex == groupindex)
520 {
521 if (subindexcount == subindex) return &_pArray[i];
522 subindexcount++;
523 }
524 if (currentindex > groupindex) return NULL;
525 }
526 return NULL;
527 }
528
536 void _RedistributeArray(CMPER cmper = 0)
537 {
538 if (cmper == 0)
539 {
540 if (GetCount() == 0) return; /* To prevent crash */
541 __FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement* pFirstInci = (__FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement*) GetItemAt(0);
542 cmper = pFirstInci->_GetDataID()->other.cmper;
543 }
544 ClearAll();
545 twobyte inci = 0;
546 __FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement* pCurrentObject = NULL;
547 for (int i = 0; i < _arraycounter; i++)
548 {
549 if (i % 2 == 0)
550 {
551 pCurrentObject = new __FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement();
552 EDataID* pDataID = (EDataID*) pCurrentObject->_GetDataID(); /* "Turn off" const */
553 pDataID->other.cmper = cmper;
554 pDataID->other.inci = inci;
555 inci++;
556 memcpy(pCurrentObject->_GetFirstRecordPtr(), &_pArray[i], sizeof(ECompositeTimeUpper));
557 }
558 else
559 {
560 memcpy(pCurrentObject->_GetSecondRecordPtr(), &_pArray[i], sizeof(ECompositeTimeUpper));
561 Add(pCurrentObject);
562 pCurrentObject = NULL;
563 }
564 }
565 if (pCurrentObject) Add(pCurrentObject);
566 }
567#endif
568
569#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
570 __FCBaseData* CreateElement() override { return new __FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement(); }
571#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
572 public:
573
574#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
576 void _BuildArray()
577 {
578 delete [] _pArray;
579 _pArray = NULL;
580 _arraycounter = 0;
581 if (GetCount() == 0) return;
582 /* Count the number of active records in the array */
583 int activerecords = 0;
584 for (int i = 0; i < GetCount(); i++)
585 {
586 __FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement* pData = (__FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement*) GetItemAt(i);
587 ECompositeTimeUpper* pCompositeTimeUpper = pData->_GetFirstRecordPtr();
588 if ((pCompositeTimeUpper->main == 0) &&
589 (pCompositeTimeUpper->fraction == 0)) continue;
590 activerecords ++;
591 pCompositeTimeUpper = pData->_GetSecondRecordPtr();
592 if ((pCompositeTimeUpper->main == 0) &&
593 (pCompositeTimeUpper->fraction == 0)) continue;
594 activerecords ++;
595 }
596 if (activerecords == 0) return;
597 // Allocate memory and copy:
598 _pArray = new ECompositeTimeUpper[activerecords];
599 int currentindex = 0;
600 for (int i = 0; i < GetCount(); i++)
601 {
602 __FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement* pData = (__FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement*) GetItemAt(i);
603 ECompositeTimeUpper* pCompositeTimeUpper = pData->_GetFirstRecordPtr();
604 if ((pCompositeTimeUpper->main == 0) &&
605 (pCompositeTimeUpper->fraction == 0)) continue;
606 memcpy(&_pArray[currentindex], pCompositeTimeUpper, sizeof(ECompositeTimeUpper));
607 currentindex ++;
608 pCompositeTimeUpper = pData->_GetSecondRecordPtr();
609 if ((pCompositeTimeUpper->main == 0) &&
610 (pCompositeTimeUpper->fraction == 0)) continue;
611 memcpy(&_pArray[currentindex], pCompositeTimeUpper, sizeof(ECompositeTimeUpper));
612 currentindex ++;
613 }
614 _arraycounter = activerecords;
615 }
616#endif
617
618 const char* ClassName() override { return "FCCompositeTimeSigTop"; }
619
621 FCCompositeTimeSigTop() : __FCCollectionInciOther()
622 {
623 _pArray = NULL;
624 _arraycounter = 0;
625 }
626
628 virtual ~FCCompositeTimeSigTop()
629 {
630 delete [] _pArray;
631 _pArray = NULL;
632 _arraycounter = 0;
633 }
634
640 int GetGroupCount()
641 {
642 int groupcount = 0;
643 for (int i = 0; i < _arraycounter; i++)
644 {
645 if (_pArray[i].chainstart) groupcount++;
646 }
647 return groupcount;
648 }
649
656 int AddGroup(int elementcount)
657 {
658 if (elementcount < 1) return -1;
659 if (elementcount > 10) return -1;
660
661 ECompositeTimeUpper* pNewArray = new ECompositeTimeUpper[_arraycounter + elementcount];
662
663 if (_pArray)
664 {
665 /* Copy the old data and remove it */
666 int bytesize = sizeof(ECompositeTimeUpper) * _arraycounter;
667 memcpy(pNewArray, _pArray, bytesize);
668 delete [] _pArray;
669 }
670
671 /* Initialize the new data */
672 ECompositeTimeUpper* pNewAddedData = &pNewArray[_arraycounter];
673 for (int i = 0; i < elementcount; i++)
674 {
675 pNewAddedData->chainstart = (i == 0);
676 pNewAddedData->fraction = 0;
677 pNewAddedData->main = 1;
678 pNewAddedData ++;
679 }
680
681 /* Set new info: */
682 _arraycounter += elementcount;
683 _pArray = pNewArray;
684
685 return GetGroupCount() - 1;
686 }
687
694 void MergeWithPreviousGroup(int groupindex)
695 {
696 if (groupindex < 1) return;
697 ECompositeTimeUpper* pData = _GetGroupElementPtr(groupindex, 0);
698 if (!pData) return;
699 pData->chainstart = false;
700 }
701
702
710 int GetGroupElementCount(int index)
711 {
712 index++; /* Make the index 1-based internally for this method */
713 int currentindex = 0;
714 int count = 0;
715 for (int i = 0; i < _arraycounter; i++)
716 {
717 if (_pArray[i].chainstart) currentindex++;
718 if (currentindex == index) count++;
719 if (currentindex > index) return count;
720 }
721 return count;
722 }
723
732 int CalcTotalGroupBeats(int groupindex)
733 {
734 int beatcount = 0;
735 int elementcount = GetGroupElementCount(groupindex);
736 for (int elementidx = 0; elementidx < elementcount; elementidx++)
737 {
738 beatcount += GetGroupElementBeats(groupindex, elementidx);
739 }
740 return beatcount;
741 }
742
750 int GetGroupElementBeats(int groupindex, int subindex)
751 {
752 ECompositeTimeUpper* pCompositeTimeUpper = _GetGroupElementPtr(groupindex, subindex);
753 if (!pCompositeTimeUpper) return 0;
754 return pCompositeTimeUpper->main;
755 }
756
759 int GetElementCount()
760 {
761 return _arraycounter;
762 }
763
771 void SetGroupElementBeats(int groupindex, int subindex, twobyte value)
772 {
773 ECompositeTimeUpper* pCompositeTimeUpper = _GetGroupElementPtr(groupindex, subindex);
774 if (!pCompositeTimeUpper) return;
775 pCompositeTimeUpper->main = value;
776 }
777
780 bool SaveAll() override
781 {
782 if (_arraycounter == 0) return false;
783 if (GetCount() == 0)
784 {
785#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DIAGNOSE
786 DebugOut("FCCompositeTimeSigTop()::SaveAll(): No existing collection items to read CMPER.");
787#endif
788 return false; /* There must be an existing CMPER to save to */
789 }
790 _RedistributeArray();
791 __FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement* pFirstInci = (__FCCompositeTimeSigTopElement*) GetItemAt(0);
792 CMPER cmper = pFirstInci->_GetDataID()->other.cmper;
793 DeleteDataForItem(cmper);
794 return __FCCollectionInciOther::SaveAll();
795 }
796
799 bool SaveAllForItem(CMPER cmper) override
800 {
801 if (_arraycounter == 0) return false;
802
803 _RedistributeArray(cmper);
804
805 if (GetCount() == 0)
806 {
807#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DIAGNOSE
808 DebugOut("FCCompositeTimeSigTop()::SaveAllForItem(): No existing collection items to read CMPER.");
809#endif
810 return false; /* There must be an existing CMPER to save to */
811 }
812
813 DeleteDataForItem(cmper);
814 __FCCollectionInciOther::SaveAll();
815
816 return true;
817 }
818};
819
820#endif /*PDK_FRAMEWORK_COMPOSITETIMESIGS*/

823#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_COMPOSITETIMESIGS
832class FCCompositeTimeSigBottom : public __FCCollectionInciOther
833{
835 ECompositeTimeLower* _pArray;
836
839 int _arraycounter;
840
841#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
846 ECompositeTimeLower* _GetGroupElementPtr(int groupindex, int subindex)
847 {
848 groupindex++; /* Make the index 1-based internally for this method */
849 int currentindex = 0;
850 int subindexcount = 0;
851 for (int i = 0; i < _arraycounter; i++)
852 {
853 if (_pArray[i].chainstart) currentindex++;
854 if (currentindex == groupindex)
855 {
856 if (subindexcount == subindex) return &_pArray[i];
857 subindexcount++;
858 }
859 if (currentindex > groupindex) return NULL;
860 }
861 return NULL;
862 }
863
870 void _RedistributeArray(CMPER cmper = 0)
871 {
872 if (cmper == 0)
873 {
874 if (GetCount() == 0) return; /* To avoid crashes */
875 __FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement* pFirstInci = (__FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement*) GetItemAt(0);
876 cmper = pFirstInci->_GetDataID()->other.cmper;
877 }
878 ClearAll();
879 twobyte inci = 0;
880 __FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement* pCurrentObject = NULL;
881 EDataID* pDataID = NULL;
882 for (int i = 0; i < _arraycounter; i++)
883 {
884 switch (i % 3) {
885 case 0:
886 pCurrentObject = new __FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement();
887 pDataID = (EDataID*) pCurrentObject->_GetDataID(); /* "Turn off" const */
888 pDataID->other.cmper = cmper;
889 pDataID->other.inci = inci;
890 inci++;
891 memcpy(pCurrentObject->_GetFirstRecordPtr(), &_pArray[i], sizeof (ECompositeTimeLower));
892 break;
893 case 1:
894 memcpy(pCurrentObject->_GetSecondRecordPtr(), &_pArray[i], sizeof (ECompositeTimeLower));
895 break;
896 default:
897 memcpy(pCurrentObject->_GetThirdRecordPtr(), &_pArray[i], sizeof (ECompositeTimeLower));
898 Add(pCurrentObject);
899 pCurrentObject = NULL;
900 break;
901 }
902 }
903 if (pCurrentObject) Add(pCurrentObject);
904 }
905#endif
906
907#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
908 __FCBaseData* CreateElement() override { return new __FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement(); }
909#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
910 public:
911
912#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
914 void _BuildArray()
915 {
916 delete [] _pArray;
917 _pArray = NULL;
918 _arraycounter = 0;
919 if (GetCount() == 0) return;
920 /* Count the number of active records in the array */
921 int activerecords = 0;
922 for (int i = 0; i < GetCount(); i++)
923 {
924 __FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement* pData = (__FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement*) GetItemAt(i);
925 ECompositeTimeLower* pCompositeTimeLower = pData->_GetFirstRecordPtr();
926 if (pCompositeTimeLower->main == 0) continue;
927 activerecords ++;
928 pCompositeTimeLower = pData->_GetSecondRecordPtr();
929 if (pCompositeTimeLower->main == 0) continue;
930 activerecords ++;
931 pCompositeTimeLower = pData->_GetThirdRecordPtr();
932 if (pCompositeTimeLower->main == 0) continue;
933 activerecords ++;
934 }
935 if (activerecords == 0) return;
936 // Allocate memory and copy:
937 _pArray = new ECompositeTimeLower[activerecords];
938 int currentindex = 0;
939 for (int i = 0; i < GetCount(); i++)
940 {
941 __FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement* pData = (__FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement*) GetItemAt(i);
942 ECompositeTimeLower* pCompositeTimeLower = pData->_GetFirstRecordPtr();
943 if (pCompositeTimeLower->main == 0) continue;
944 memcpy(&_pArray[currentindex], pCompositeTimeLower, sizeof(ECompositeTimeLower));
945 currentindex ++;
946 pCompositeTimeLower = pData->_GetSecondRecordPtr();
947 if (pCompositeTimeLower->main == 0) continue;
948 memcpy(&_pArray[currentindex], pCompositeTimeLower, sizeof(ECompositeTimeLower));
949 currentindex ++;
950 pCompositeTimeLower = pData->_GetThirdRecordPtr();
951 if (pCompositeTimeLower->main == 0) continue;
952 memcpy(&_pArray[currentindex], pCompositeTimeLower, sizeof(ECompositeTimeLower));
953 currentindex ++;
954 }
955 _arraycounter = activerecords;
956 }
957#endif

981 int GetGroupCount()

998 int GetGroupElementCount(int groupindex)
999 {
1000 groupindex++; /* Make the index 1-based internally for this method */
1001 int currentindex = 0;
1002 int count = 0;
1003 for (int i = 0; i < _arraycounter; i++)
1004 {

1006 if (currentindex == groupindex) count++;
1007 if (currentindex > groupindex) return count;
1008 }

1011
1021 int GetGroupElementBeatDuration(int groupindex, int subindex)
1022 {
1023 ECompositeTimeLower* pCompositeTimeLower = _GetGroupElementPtr(groupindex, subindex);
1024 if (!pCompositeTimeLower) return 0;
1025 return pCompositeTimeLower->main;
1026 }
1027
1030 int GetElementCount()
1031 {
1032 return _arraycounter;
1033 }
1034
1039 int AddGroup()
1040 {
1041 ECompositeTimeLower* pNewArray = new ECompositeTimeLower[_arraycounter + 1];
1042
1043 if (_pArray)
1044 {
1045 /* Copy the old data and remove it */
1046 int bytesize = sizeof(ECompositeTimeLower) * _arraycounter;
1047 memcpy(pNewArray, _pArray, bytesize);
1048 delete [] _pArray;
1049 }
1050
1051 /* Initialize the new data */
1052 ECompositeTimeLower* pNewAddedData = &pNewArray[_arraycounter];
1053 pNewAddedData->chainstart = true;
1054 pNewAddedData->main = 1024;
1055 pNewAddedData ++;
1056
1057 /* Set new info: */
1058 _arraycounter ++;
1059 _pArray = pNewArray;
1060
1061 return GetGroupCount() - 1;
1062 }
1063
1070 bool DeleteGroup(int groupindex)
1071 {
1072 if (groupindex < 0) return false;
1073 if (groupindex >= GetElementCount()) return false;
1074
1075 /* Assumes that all groups are one element long!!! */
1076 for (int idx = groupindex; idx < _arraycounter - 1; idx ++)
1077 {
1078 TimeEdu32 value = GetGroupElementBeatDuration(idx + 1, 0);
1079 SetGroupElementBeatDuration(idx, 0, value);
1080 }
1081
1082 _arraycounter --;
1083 return true;
1084 }
1085
1092 void SetGroupElementBeatDuration(int groupindex, int subindex, twobyte value)
1093 {
1094 ECompositeTimeLower* pCompositeTimeLower = _GetGroupElementPtr(groupindex, subindex);
1095 if (!pCompositeTimeLower) return;
1096 pCompositeTimeLower->main = value;
1097 }
1098
1101 bool SaveAll() override
1102 {
1103 if (_arraycounter == 0) return false;
1104 if (GetCount() == 0)
1105 {
1106#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DIAGNOSE
1107 DebugOut("FCCompositeTimeSigBottom()::SaveAll(): No existing collection items to read CMPER.");
1108#endif
1109 return false; /* There must be an existing CMPER to save to */
1110 }
1111 _RedistributeArray();
1112 __FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement* pFirstInci = (__FCCompositeTimeSigBottomElement*) GetItemAt(0);
1113 CMPER cmper = pFirstInci->_GetDataID()->other.cmper;
1114 DeleteDataForItem(cmper);
1115 return __FCCollectionInciOther::SaveAll();
1116 }
1117
1120 bool SaveAllForItem(CMPER cmper) override
1121 {
1122 if (_arraycounter == 0) return false;
1123 _RedistributeArray(cmper);
1124 if (GetCount() == 0)
1125 {
1126#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DIAGNOSE
1127 DebugOut("FCCompositeTimeSigBottom()::SaveAllForItem(): No existing collection items to read CMPER.");
1128#endif
1129 return false; /* There must be an existing CMPER to save to */
1130 }
1131
1132 DeleteDataForItem(cmper);
1133 __FCCollectionInciOther::SaveAll();
1134
1135 return true;
1136 }
1137};
1138#endif

1308 bool IsIdentical(__FCBase* pTestObject) override
1309 {
1310 FCShapeDefInstruction* pTestInstruction = dynamic_cast<FCShapeDefInstruction*>(pTestObject);
1311 if(!pTestInstruction) return false;
1312 if (GetCount() != pTestInstruction->GetCount()) return false;
1313 if (GetTag() != pTestInstruction->GetTag()) return false;
1314 int count = GetCount();
1315 for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)
1316 {
1317 if (GetFourbyteData(i) != pTestInstruction->GetFourbyteData(i)) return false;
1318 }
1319 return true;
1320 }

1327 const char* GetTagAsString() const
1328 {
1329 _tagstring.Clear();
1330 switch (GetTag()) {
1331 case st_setfont:
1332 _tagstring.SetCString("setfont");
1333 break;
1334 case st_startobject:
1335 _tagstring.SetCString("startobject");
1336 break;
1337 case st_startgroup:
1338 _tagstring.SetCString("startgroup");
1339 break;
1340 case st_endgroup:
1341 _tagstring.SetCString("endgroup");
1342 break;
1343 case st_drawchar:
1344 _tagstring.SetCString("drawchar");
1345 break;
1346 case st_stroke:
1347 _tagstring.SetCString("stroke");
1348 break;
1349 case st_rmoveto:
1350 _tagstring.SetCString("rmoveto");
1351 break;
1352 case st_linewidth:
1353 _tagstring.SetCString("linewidth");
1354 break;
1355 case st_setdash:
1356 _tagstring.SetCString("setdash");
1357 break;
1358 case st_rlineto:
1359 _tagstring.SetCString("rlineto");
1360 break;
1361 case st_setgray:
1362 _tagstring.SetCString("setgrey");
1363 break;
1364 case st_ellipse:
1365 _tagstring.SetCString("ellipse");
1366 break;
1367 case st_fillsolid:
1368 _tagstring.SetCString("fillsolid");
1369 break;
1370 case st_curveto:
1371 _tagstring.SetCString("curveto");
1372 break;
1373 case st_slur:
1374 _tagstring.SetCString("slur");
1375 break;
1376 case st_rectangle:
1377 _tagstring.SetCString("rectangle");
1378 break;
1379 case st_closepath:
1380 _tagstring.SetCString("closepath");
1381 break;
1382 case st_bracket:
1383 _tagstring.SetCString("bracket");
1384 break;
1385 case 0:
1386 _tagstring.SetCString("Null");
1387 break;
1388 default:
1389 _tagstring.AppendCharacter((GetTag() & 0xff00) / 256);
1390 _tagstring.AppendCharacter(GetTag() & 0xff);
1391 break;
1392 }
1393
1394 return _tagstring.GetCString();
1395 }

2095#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_SHAPES
2096#define __ot_Shape_WORKAROUNDTAG MAKEEXTAG(edOther,'S','D')
2097
2113class FCShapeDef : public __FCNoInciOther
2114{
2115public:
2118 enum SHAPEDEF_TYPES
2119 {
2120 SHAPEDEFTYPE_UNKNOWN = -1,
2121 SHAPEDEFTYPE_OTHER = 0,
2122 SHAPEDEFTYPE_ARTICULATION = 1,
2123 SHAPEDEFTYPE_BARLINE = 2,
2124 SHAPEDEFTYPE_EXECUTABLESHAPE = 3,
2125 SHAPEDEFTYPE_EXPRESSION = 4,
2126 SHAPEDEFTYPE_NOTE = 5,
2127 SHAPEDEFTYPE_FRAME = 6,
2128 SHAPEDEFTYPE_ARROWHEAD = 7,
2129 SHAPEDEFTYPE_FRETBOARD = 8,
2130 SHAPEDEFTYPE_CLEF = 9
2131 };
2132
2133private:
2134#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
2135 EDTShape* _TypeCast() const { return (EDTShape*)_datablock; }
2136#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014B
2137 EDTShape2014b* _TypeCast2014b() const { return (EDTShape2014b*)_datablock; }
2138#endif
2139 /* _isemptyshape & _shapedeftype are used for pre2014b, to
2140 try to work around load crashes for empty shapes on Windows */
2141 bool _isemptyshape;
2142 SHAPEDEF_TYPES _shapedeftype;
2143
2144 void _AllocateMemory(int size)
2145 {
2146 if (size == 0)
2147 {
2148 _datablock = NULL;
2149 _loadedsize = 0;
2150 return;
2151 }
2152 _datablock = new char [size];
2153 memset(_datablock, 0, size);
2154 _loadedsize = size;
2155 }
2156
2157 bool _Is2014Format() const;
2158
2159 bool _Is2014bFormat() const;
2160
2165 bool _SaveType(SHAPEDEF_TYPES shapedeftype)
2166 {
2167 /* On Fin2014b, the shape type is available in the struct. */
2168 if (_Is2014bFormat()) return true;
2169
2170 twobyte oneinci[6];
2171 EDataID dataID;
2172 dataID.other.cmper = _dataid.other.cmper;
2173 dataID.other.inci = 0;
2174 fourbyte size = sizeof(oneinci);
2175 /* Load the raw data (no special extag!) */
2176 if (!FX_LoadEData(__ot_Shape_WORKAROUNDTAG, &dataID, &oneinci, &size)) return false;
2177 oneinci[2] = (twobyte) shapedeftype;
2178 _shapedeftype = shapedeftype;
2179 return FX_SaveEData(__ot_Shape_WORKAROUNDTAG, &dataID, &oneinci, size) != 0;
2180 }
2181
2186 bool _LoadType()
2187 {
2188 /* On Fin2014b, the shape type is available in the struct */
2189 if (_Is2014bFormat()) return true;
2190
2191 twobyte oneinci[6];
2192 EDataID dataID;
2193 dataID.other.cmper = _dataid.other.cmper;
2194 dataID.other.inci = 0;
2195 fourbyte size = sizeof(oneinci);
2196 /* Load the raw data (no special extag!) */
2197 if (!FX_LoadEData(__ot_Shape_WORKAROUNDTAG, &dataID, &oneinci, &size)) return false;
2198 _shapedeftype = (SHAPEDEF_TYPES) oneinci[2];
2199 return true;
2200 }
2201
2202protected:
2205 EXTAG Tag() override { return GetCustomTag() ? GetCustomTag() : ot_Shape; }
2206
2207 EVERSION EnigmaVersion() override;
2208
2209 void CloneMemoryFrom(__FCBaseData* pSource) override
2210 {
2211 /* Copy the heap: */
2212 __FCNoInciOther::CloneMemoryFrom(pSource);
2213 /* Copy the empty shape state */
2214 _isemptyshape = ((FCShapeDef*) pSource)->_GetIsEmptyShape();
2215 }

2217 int DataSizeLoad() override
2218 {
2219 fourbyte size;
2220 if (!FX_LoadEData(Tag(), &_dataid, NULL, &size, EnigmaVersion())) return 0;
2221
2222 if (!_Is2014bFormat())
2223 {
2224 /* Attempt to workaround for empty shape crashes on earlier Finale versions. */
2225 SetCustomTag((size == sizeof(EDTShape)) ? __ot_Shape_WORKAROUNDTAG : ot_Shape);
2226 }
2227 return size;
2228 }

2287
2297 bool _EmptyShapeCheck(CMPER cmper, bool* pIsEmpty)
2298 {
2299#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DIAGNOSE
2300 if (_Is2014bFormat())
2301 {
2302 DebugOut("FCShapeDef::_EmptyShapeCheck was called on 2014b struct.");
2303 return false;
2304 }
2305#endif
2306
2307 *pIsEmpty = true;
2308 //twobyte shapetestinci[6];
2309 EDTShape shapetest;
2310 memset(&shapetest, 0, sizeof(shapetest));
2311 EDataID dataID;
2312 dataID.other.cmper = cmper;
2313 dataID.other.inci = 0;
2314 fourbyte size = sizeof(shapetest);
2315 /* Load the raw data (no special extag) */
2316 bool result = FX_LoadEData(__ot_Shape_WORKAROUNDTAG,
2317 &dataID, &shapetest, &size, EnigmaVersion()) != 0;
2318 if (!result) return false;
2319 int loopcount = size / sizeof(twobyte);
2320 twobyte* pNonZeroCheck = (twobyte*) &shapetest;
2321 for (int i = 0; i < loopcount; i++)
2322 {
2323 if (pNonZeroCheck[i])
2324 {
2325 if (i == 1) continue; /* On the 1st twobyte (0-based), there might
2326 be data even for empty shapes!!! */
2327 if (i == 2) continue; /* On the 2nd twobyte (0-based), there might
2328 be data even for empty shapes!!! */
2329 *pIsEmpty = false;
2330 return true;
2331 }
2332 }
2333 return true;
2334 }

2370 bool CalcProtected()
2371 {
2372 if (_Is2014bFormat()) return false;
2373
2374 EDataID dataID;
2375 twobyte buffer[6];
2376 dataID.other.cmper = GetItemNo();
2377 dataID.other.inci = 0;
2378 fourbyte size = sizeof(buffer);
2379 memset(buffer, 0, sizeof(buffer));
2380 if (!FX_LoadEData(__ot_Shape_WORKAROUNDTAG, &dataID, buffer, &size, FINALEVERSION_2010)) return false;
2381 return ((buffer[2] & 0x0008) != 0);
2382 }

2391 {

2394 }

2397 bool LoadNext() override
2398 {
2399 return Load(GetItemNo() + 1);
2400 }
2401
2405 bool Load(CMPER itemno) override
2406 {
2407 bool isemptyshape;
2408
2409 bool result = false;
2410 if (_Is2014bFormat())
2411 {
2412 /* Normal load */
2413 result = __FCNoInciOther::Load(itemno);
2414 if (result)
2415 {
2416#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014B
2417 _shapedeftype = (SHAPEDEF_TYPES) _TypeCast2014b()->shapeType;
2418 /* _isemptyshape shouldn't actively be used on 2014b+ */
2419 _isemptyshape = (_TypeCast2014b()->instrucLen == 0);
2420#endif
2421 }
2422 else
2423 {
2424 _shapedeftype = SHAPEDEFTYPE_UNKNOWN;
2425 _isemptyshape = true;
2426 }
2427 }
2428 else
2429 {
2430 /* On pre2014b, try to work around the empty shape crash bug */
2431 if (!_EmptyShapeCheck(itemno, &isemptyshape)) return false;
2432 SetCustomTag(isemptyshape ? __ot_Shape_WORKAROUNDTAG : ot_Shape);
2433 _isemptyshape = isemptyshape;
2434 result = __FCNoInciOther::Load(itemno);
2435 if (result)
2436 _LoadType();
2437 else
2438 _shapedeftype = SHAPEDEFTYPE_UNKNOWN;
2439 }
2440 return result;
2441 }

2460#endif

2463 if (_Is2014bFormat())

2566 fourbyte GetInstructionsCount() const
2567 {
2568 int returnval = 0;
2569 if (_Is2014bFormat())
2570 {
2571#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014B
2572 /* On 2014b+, _isemptyshape shouldn't be used. */
2573 returnval = _TypeCast2014b()->instrucLen;
2574#endif
2575 }
2576 else
2577 {
2578 returnval = _isemptyshape ? 0 : _TypeCast()->instrucLen;
2579 /* Have some range check, since empty shapes can have
2580 very strange values on earlier Finale versions. */
2581 if ((returnval > 300) || (returnval < 0)) return -1;
2582 }
2583 return returnval;

2951 ENCLOSURESHAPE
2952#else

2954#endif
2955 shape)

3066 void SetMode(
3067#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
3068 ENCLOSUREMODES
3069#else
3070 int
3071#endif
3072 enclosuremode)
3073 {
3074 switch (enclosuremode)
3075 {
3076 case ENCLOSUREMODE_NONE:
3077 Set16BitFlag((FLAG_16*)_GetFlagPtr(), NOT_TALL, false);
3078 Set16BitFlag((FLAG_16*)_GetFlagPtr(), EQUAL_ASPECT, false);
3079 break;
3080 case ENCLOSUREMODE_MINWIDTH:
3081 Set16BitFlag((FLAG_16*)_GetFlagPtr(), NOT_TALL, true);
3082 Set16BitFlag((FLAG_16*)_GetFlagPtr(), EQUAL_ASPECT, false);
3083 break;
3084 case ENCLOSUREMODE_MATCHDIMENSIONS:
3085 Set16BitFlag((FLAG_16*)_GetFlagPtr(), NOT_TALL, false);
3086 Set16BitFlag((FLAG_16*)_GetFlagPtr(), EQUAL_ASPECT, true);
3087 break;
3088 }
3089 }

5130 FCKeySignature* GetKeySignature() const {

5132 if (_pKeySig) return _pKeySig;
5133 if (!_pKeySig) _pKeySig = new FCKeySignature();
5134#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014

5153

5163
5178 FCTimeSignature* GetTimeSignature() const
5179 {
5180 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return NULL;
5181 if (_pTimeSig) return _pTimeSig;
5182 if (!_pTimeSig) _pTimeSig = new FCTimeSignature();
5183#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014
5184 if (_VersionToUse() == FINALEVERSION_2014)
5185 {
5186 _pTimeSig->SetBeats(_measurespec2014.beats);
5187 _pTimeSig->SetBeatDuration(_measurespec2014.divbeat);
5188 } else
5189#endif
5190 {
5191 _pTimeSig->SetBeats(_measurespec2005.beats);
5192 _pTimeSig->SetBeatDuration(_measurespec2005.divbeat);
5193 }
5194 _pTimeSig->SetCompositeTop(_GetAuxFlag(MEAS_ALTNUMTSIG));
5195 _pTimeSig->SetCompositeBottom(_GetAuxFlag(MEAS_ALTDENTSIG));
5196 _pTimeSig->SetAbbreviate(false);
5197 return _pTimeSig;
5198 }
5199
5210 FCTimeSignature* GetTimeSignatureForDisplay() const
5211 {
5212 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return NULL;
5213 if (!GetUseTimeSigForDisplay()) return NULL;
5214 if (_pTimeSigDisplay) return _pTimeSigDisplay;
5215 if (!_pTimeSigDisplay) _pTimeSigDisplay = new FCTimeSignature();
5216#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014
5217 if (_VersionToUse() == FINALEVERSION_2014)
5218 {
5219 _pTimeSigDisplay->SetBeats(_measurespec2014.dispBeats);
5220 _pTimeSigDisplay->SetBeatDuration(_measurespec2014.dispDivbeat);
5221 } else
5222#endif
5223 {
5224 _pTimeSigDisplay->SetBeats(_measurespec2005.dispBeats);
5225 _pTimeSigDisplay->SetBeatDuration(_measurespec2005.dispDivbeat);
5226 }
5227 _pTimeSigDisplay->SetCompositeTop(_GetNewFlag(MEAS_DISPLAY_ALTNUMTSIG));
5228 _pTimeSigDisplay->SetCompositeBottom(_GetNewFlag(MEAS_DISPLAY_ALTDENTSIG));
5229 _pTimeSigDisplay->SetAbbreviate(_GetNewFlag(MEAS_ABBRVTIME));
5230 return _pTimeSigDisplay;
5231 }
5232
5242 void SetUseTimeSigForDisplay(bool value)
5243 {
5244 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return;
5245 if (GetUseTimeSigForDisplay() == value) return;
5246 if (!value)
5247 {
5248 if (_pTimeSigDisplay)
5249 {
5250 delete _pTimeSigDisplay;
5251 _pTimeSigDisplay = NULL;
5252 }
5253 }
5254 return _SetNewFlag(MEAS_USE_DISPLAY_TIMESIG, value);
5255 }
5256};

6653 {
6654 if (measureno > GetEndMeasure()) return false;
6655 if (measureno < GetStartMeasure()) return false;
6656 return true;
6657 }

6675

6689 {
6690 /* Store the "actual" value, restore it with _RestoreTempNonIncludedMeasures() */
6691 _pTempNonIncludedMeasuresStorage = _pNonIncludedMeasures;
6692 /* Set temp value */
6693 _pNonIncludedMeasures = pNonNumberedMeasuresToUse;
6694 }
6695
6700 void _RestoreTempNonIncludedMeasures()
6701 {
6702 /* Restore from temporary storage to the "real" storage */
6703 _pNonIncludedMeasures = _pTempNonIncludedMeasuresStorage;
6704 }

6844
6851 bool DeleteResizeData()
6852 {
6853 if (_dataid.other.cmper == 0) return false;
6854 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return false;
6855 EDataID dataID;
6856 dataID.detail.cmper1 = _dataid.other.cmper; /* System */
6857 dataID.detail.cmper2 = _instrumentused.inst; /* Staff */
6858 dataID.detail.inci = 0; /* Should be 0 */
6859 return FX_DeleteEData(dt_StaffEnduction, &dataID, EnigmaVersion()) != 0;
6860 }
6861

6864 {

7079

7085
7092 void SetJustification(FLAG_16 justification)
7093 {
7094 justification &= NAMEPOS_JUSTIBITS;
7095 _namepos.flag &= ~NAMEPOS_JUSTIBITS;
7096 _namepos.flag |= justification;
7097 }
7098
7105 void SetAlignment(FLAG_16 alignment)
7106 {
7107 alignment = alignment << 4;
7108 alignment &= NAMEPOS_HALIGNBITS;
7109 _namepos.flag &= ~NAMEPOS_HALIGNBITS;
7110 _namepos.flag |= alignment;
7111 }

7119 Set16BitFlag(&_namepos.flag, NAMEPOS_EXPAND_SINGLE_WORD, state);
7120 }

7133

9743#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2012
9754 const char* GetInstrumentUUID() const
9755 {
9756 if (_VersionToUse() < FINALEVERSION_2012) return "";
9757 _uuid.Clear();
9758
9759 const uonebyte* pInstUUID = _GetInstUUIDPtr();
9760 for (int i = 0; i < UUID_SIZE_PDK; i++)
9761 {
9762 uonebyte abyte = pInstUUID[i];
9763 int highnibble = (abyte & 0xf0) >> 4;
9764 int lownibble = (abyte & 0x0f);
9765 if (highnibble < 10)
9766 _uuid.AppendCharacter(highnibble + '0');
9767 else
9768 _uuid.AppendCharacter(highnibble + 'a' - 10);
9769 if (lownibble < 10)
9770 _uuid.AppendCharacter(lownibble + '0');
9771 else
9772 _uuid.AppendCharacter(lownibble + 'a' - 10);
9773 switch (i)
9774 {
9775 case 3:
9776 case 5:
9777 case 7:
9778 case 9:
9779 _uuid.AppendCharacter('-');
9780 break;
9781 }
9782 }
9783 return _uuid.GetCString();
9784 }
9785#endif

10523#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2012
10538 void SetInstrumentUUID(const char* pszUUID)
10539 {
10540 if (_VersionToUse() < FINALEVERSION_2012) return;
10541 if (!pszUUID) return;
10542 if (strlen(pszUUID) != 36) return; /* Wrong string format */
10543 if (pszUUID[8] != '-') return; /* No first dash */
10544 if (pszUUID[13] != '-') return; /* No second dash */
10545 if (pszUUID[18] != '-') return; /* No third dash */
10546 if (pszUUID[23] != '-') return; /* No fourth dash */
10547 for (int i = 0; i < 36; i++)
10548 {
10549 switch (i)
10550 {
10551 case 8:
10552 case 13:
10553 case 18:
10554 case 23:
10555 if (pszUUID[i] != '-') return;
10556 break;
10557 default:
10558 if ((pszUUID[i] >= 'a') && (pszUUID[i] <= 'f')) break;
10559 if ((pszUUID[i] >= '0') && (pszUUID[i] <= '9')) break;
10560 return;
10561 }
10562 }
10563 /* UUID validation ok - store the UUID */
10564 const char* pszCurrent = pszUUID;
10565 for (int i = 0; i < UUID_SIZE_PDK; i++)
10566 {
10567 int result1, result2;
10568 if (*pszCurrent >= 'a') result1 = *pszCurrent - 'a' + 10;
10569 else if (*pszCurrent >= 'A') result1 = *pszCurrent - 'A' + 10;
10570 else result1 = *pszCurrent - '0';
10571 pszCurrent ++;
10572 if (*pszCurrent >= 'a') result2 = *pszCurrent - 'a' + 10;
10573 else if (*pszCurrent >= 'A') result2 = *pszCurrent - 'A' + 10;
10574 else result2 = *pszCurrent - '0';
10575 int result = (result1 * 0x10) | result2;
10576 uonebyte* pInstUUID = (uonebyte*) _GetInstUUIDPtr();
10577 pInstUUID[i] = result;
10578 pszCurrent ++;
10579 if ((i == 3) || (i == 5) || (i == 7) || (i == 9)) pszCurrent ++;
10580 }
10581 }
10582#endif

10870#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2012
10880 bool InstrumentMatchesUUID(const char* pszUUID)
10881 {
10882 if (_VersionToUse() < FINALEVERSION_2012) return false;
10883 uonebyte* pInstUUID = (uonebyte*) _GetInstUUIDPtr();
10884
10885 if (strlen(pszUUID) != 36) return false; /* Wrong string format */
10886 if (pszUUID[8] != '-') return false; /* No first dash */
10887 if (pszUUID[13] != '-') return false; /* No second dash */
10888 if (pszUUID[18] != '-') return false; /* No third dash */
10889 if (pszUUID[23] != '-') return false; /* No fourth dash */
10890 const char* pszCurrent = pszUUID;
10891 for (int i = 0; i < UUID_SIZE_PDK; i++)
10892 {
10893 int result1, result2;
10894 if (*pszCurrent >= 'a') result1 = *pszCurrent - 'a' + 10;
10895 else if (*pszCurrent >= 'A') result1 = *pszCurrent - 'A' + 10;
10896 else result1 = *pszCurrent - '0';
10897 pszCurrent ++;
10898 if (*pszCurrent >= 'a') result2 = *pszCurrent - 'a' + 10;
10899 else if (*pszCurrent >= 'A') result2 = *pszCurrent - 'A' + 10;
10900 else result2 = *pszCurrent - '0';
10901 int result = (result1 * 0x10) | result2;
10902 if (result != pInstUUID[i]) return false;
10903 pszCurrent ++;
10904 if ((i == 3) || (i == 5) || (i == 7) || (i == 9)) pszCurrent ++;
10905 }
10906 return true;
10907 }
10908#endif
10909
10910#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2012
10923 bool HasInstrumentAssigned()
10924 {
10925 if (_VersionToUse() < FINALEVERSION_2012) return false;
10926 uonebyte* pInstUUID = (uonebyte*) _GetInstUUIDPtr();
10927 bool blockisempty = true;
10928 for (int i = 0; i < UUID_SIZE_PDK; i++) if (pInstUUID[i]) blockisempty = false;
10929 if (blockisempty) return false;
10930 if (InstrumentMatchesUUID(FFUUID_BLANKSTAFF)) return false;
10931 if (InstrumentMatchesUUID(FFUUID_UNKNOWN)) return false;
10932 return true;
10933 }
10934#endif
10935
10936
10937};

10940/* Macro to only refer to the EDTStaffSpec2012 on 2012 PDKs and later. */

10943#else
10944#define PROTECTED2012STAFFSPEC(code)
10945#endif
10946
10947/* Macro to only refer to the EDTStaffSpec2014 on 2014 PDKs and later. */
10948#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014
10949#define PROTECTED2014STAFFSPEC(code) code
10950#else
10951#define PROTECTED2014STAFFSPEC(code)
10952#endif
10953
10954
10960class FCStaff : public __FCStaffBase
10961{
10962
10963private:
10964#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_PREFS
10966 FCStaffNamePosition* _pFullNamePosition;
10967 FCStaffNamePosition* _pAbbreviatedNamePosition;
10968#endif
10969
10970protected:
10971#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
10978 EDTStaffSpec2010 _staffspec2010;
10979 PROTECTED2012STAFFSPEC(EDTStaffSpec2012 _staffspec2012;)
10980 PROTECTED2014STAFFSPEC(EDTStaffSpec2014 _staffspec2014;)
10981
10982 EXTAG Tag() override { return ot_EDTStaffSpec; }
10983 int DataSizeLoad() override
10984 {
10985 switch (_VersionToUse())
10986 {
10987 case FINALEVERSION_2010:
10988 return sizeof(EDTStaffSpec2010);
10989 case FINALEVERSION_2012:
10990 PROTECTED2012STAFFSPEC(return sizeof(EDTStaffSpec2012));
10991 break;
10992 default:
10993 PROTECTED2014STAFFSPEC(return sizeof(EDTStaffSpec2014));
10994 break;
10995 }
10996 }
10997 void* Allocate() override
10998 {
10999 switch (_VersionToUse())
11000 {
11001 case FINALEVERSION_2010:
11002 return (void*) &_staffspec2010;
11003#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2012
11004 case FINALEVERSION_2012:
11005 return (void*) &_staffspec2012;
11006#endif
11007 default:
11008 PROTECTED2014STAFFSPEC(return (void*) &_staffspec2014);
11009 return NULL;
11010 }
11011 }
11012
11017 void CloneMemoryFrom(__FCBaseData* pSource) override
11018 {
11019 void* pStaffSpec = NULL;
11020 fourbyte size = 0;
11021 switch (_VersionToUse())
11022 {
11023 case FINALEVERSION_2010:
11024 pStaffSpec = &_staffspec2010;
11025 size = sizeof(_staffspec2010);
11026 break;
11027 case FINALEVERSION_2012:
11028 PROTECTED2012STAFFSPEC(
11029 pStaffSpec = &_staffspec2012;
11030 size = sizeof(_staffspec2012);)
11031 break;
11032 default:
11033 PROTECTED2014STAFFSPEC(
11034 pStaffSpec = &_staffspec2014;
11035 size = sizeof(_staffspec2014);)
11036 break;
11037 }
11038
11039 memcpy(pStaffSpec, ((FCStaff*)pSource)->_GetStaffSpec(), size);
11040 _datablock = pStaffSpec;
11041 _loadedsize = size;

11296
11302 FCStaff() : __FCStaffBase()
11303 {
11304#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_PREFS
11305 _pFullNamePosition = NULL;
11306 _pAbbreviatedNamePosition = NULL;
11307#endif
11308
11309 int size = 0;
11310 switch (_VersionToUse())
11311 {
11312 case FINALEVERSION_2010:
11313 size = sizeof(_staffspec2010);
11314 memset(&_staffspec2010, 0, size);
11315 break;
11316 case FINALEVERSION_2012:
11317 PROTECTED2012STAFFSPEC(size = sizeof(_staffspec2012);)
11318 PROTECTED2012STAFFSPEC(memset(&_staffspec2012, 0, size));
11319 break;
11320 default:
11321 PROTECTED2014STAFFSPEC(size = sizeof(_staffspec2014);)
11322 PROTECTED2014STAFFSPEC(memset(&_staffspec2014, 0, size));
11323 break;
11324 }
11325 }
11326

11328 {
11329#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_PREFS

11331 _pFullNamePosition = NULL;
11332
11333 delete _pAbbreviatedNamePosition;
11334 _pAbbreviatedNamePosition = NULL;
11335#endif
11336 }

12965 virtual bool IsIdentical(__FCBase* pObject) override
12966 {
12967 FCCategoryDef* pOtherCategory = dynamic_cast<FCCategoryDef*>(pObject);
12968 if (!pOtherCategory) return false;
12969 if (pOtherCategory->GetID() != GetID()) return false;
12970 if (*pOtherCategory->_GetFlagPtr() != *_GetFlagPtr()) return false;
12971 FCString thisname, othername;
12972 pOtherCategory->GetName(&othername);
12973 GetName(&thisname);
12974 return othername.IsEqualString(&thisname);
12975 }

13396 void SetName(FCString* pString)
13397 {
13398 if (!pString) return;
13399 /* Make sure there isn't any overflow of the text */
13400 FCString tempstring;
13401 tempstring.SetString(pString);
13402 tempstring.TruncateAt(63);
13403 /* Copy the text */
13404 if (_Use2012Version())
13405 {
13406#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2012
13407 int len = tempstring.GetLength();
13408 memcpy(_categorydef2012.name, tempstring._GetUnicodeBuffer(), (len + 1) * sizeof (eUniChar16));
13409 _categorydef2012.name[len] = 0; /* For safety add a NULL */
13410#endif
13411 }
13412 else
13413 {
13414 strcpy(_categorydefold.name, tempstring.GetCString());
13415 }
13416 }

13629 FCFreezeSystem() : __FCNoInciOther()
13630 {
13631 memset(&_freezemeasures, 0, sizeof(_freezemeasures));
13632 _freezemeasures.mode = 1;
13633 _datablock = &_freezemeasures;
13634 _loadedsize = sizeof(_freezemeasures);
13635 }
13636
13645 void SetNextSysMeasure(twobyte measure) { _freezemeasures.measure = measure; }
13646
13654 twobyte GetNextSysMeasure() const { return _freezemeasures.measure; }
13655
13656
13657#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DEBUG
13658 void DebugDump() override
13659 {
13660 __FCNoInciOther::DebugDump();
13661 DebugOutInt("Next system measure: ", GetNextSysMeasure());
13662 }
13663#endif
13664};

14697 FCCategoryDef::HORIZ_JUSTIFICATION
14698#else
14699 int
14700#endif
14701 GetHorizontalJustification() const
14702 {
14703 twobyte setting; /* Shape expr def have another order than text expr defs */
14704#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014
14705 setting = (FCCategoryDef::HORIZ_JUSTIFICATION) _TypeCast()->horzExprAlign;
14706#else
14707 setting = (FCCategoryDef::HORIZ_JUSTIFICATION) _TypeCast()->measExprAlign;
14708#endif
14709 switch (setting)
14710 {
14711 case 0:
14712 return FCCategoryDef::EXPRJUSTIFY_LEFT;
14713 case 1:
14714 return FCCategoryDef::EXPRJUSTIFY_CENTER;
14715 default:
14716 return FCCategoryDef::EXPRJUSTIFY_RIGHT;
14717 }
14718
14719 }

14909
14917 void SetHorizontalJustification(
14918#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
14919 FCCategoryDef::HORIZ_JUSTIFICATION
14920#else
14921 int
14922#endif
14923 value)
14924 {
14925 /* Shape expr defs have the flags in another way than text expr defs... */
14926 twobyte setting = 0;
14927 switch (value)
14928 {
14929 case FCCategoryDef::EXPRJUSTIFY_LEFT:
14930 setting = 0;
14931 break;
14932 case FCCategoryDef::EXPRJUSTIFY_CENTER:
14933 setting = 1;
14934 break;
14935 case FCCategoryDef::EXPRJUSTIFY_RIGHT:
14936 setting = 2;
14937 break;
14938 }
14939#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014
14940 _TypeCast()->horzExprAlign = (twobyte) setting;
14941#else
14942 _TypeCast()->measExprAlign = (twobyte) setting;
14943#endif
14944 }

14954#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
14955 FCCategoryDef::HORIZ_ALIGNMENT
14956#else
14957 int
14958#endif
14959 value)
14960 {
14961#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014
14962 _TypeCast()->horzMeasExprAlign = (twobyte) value;
14963#else
14964 _TypeCast()->measAlign = (twobyte) value;
14965#endif
14966 }
14967
14972 void SetUseCategoryPos(bool value)
14973 {
14974#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_2014
14975 Set16BitFlag((FLAG_16*) &_TypeCast()->category, USE_CATEGORY_POS_MASK, value);

16233 }

16247 {

16249 Set16BitFlag(&_pagetext.flag, PAGETEXT_VPOS_PAGE_EDGE, state);
16250 }
16251
16258 void SetFrameEdgeRef(bool state)
16259 {
16260 FCTextBlock textblock;
16261 if (!textblock.Load(GetTextBlockID())) return;
16262 textblock.SetFrameReference(state);
16263 }
16264
16266 bool DeepDeleteData() override
16267 {
16268 FCTextBlock textblock;
16269 textblock.Load(GetTextBlockID());
16270 textblock.DeepDeleteData();
16271 return DeleteData();
16272 }

16937
16944 void SetPlaybackStart(
16945#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
16946 EXPRESSION_PLAYBACK_STARTPOINTS
16947#else
16948 int
16949#endif
16950 value
16951 )
16952 {
16953 switch (value)
16954 {
16955 case EXPRPLAYSTART_POSINMEASURE:
16956 Set16BitFlag(&_expression.flag, 0x0400, true);
16957 Set16BitFlag(&_expression.flag, 0x0200, false);
16958 break;
16959 case EXPRPLAYSTART_ALIGNMENTPOINT:
16960 Set16BitFlag(&_expression.flag, 0x0400, false);
16961 Set16BitFlag(&_expression.flag, 0x0200, true);
16962 break;
16963 default: /* EXPRPLAYSTART_BEGINNINGOFMEASURE */
16964 Set16BitFlag(&_expression.flag, 0x0400, false);
16965 Set16BitFlag(&_expression.flag, 0x0200, false);
16966 break;
16967 }
16968 }

17076/* Macro for accessing same-name fields in different versions
17077 of the Staff Style Def struct: */
17078#define __STAFFSTYLEDEF_RETURN_FIELD_PTR(field) \
17079switch (_VersionToUse()) \
17080{ \
17081 case FINALEVERSION_2014: \
17082 return &_staffstyledef2014.field; \
17083 case FINALEVERSION_2012: \
17084 return &_staffstyledef2012.field; \
17085 default: \
17086 return &_staffstyledef2010.field; \
17087} \

17307
17309 bool LoadFirst() override
17310 {
17311 /* Since there can be holes in the staff style "chain", there
17312 need to be a better method to find items. Scanning a gap of 20 items
17313 should be an ok workaround for most documents. */
17314 for (int i = 1; i <= 20; i++)
17315 {
17316 if (Load(i)) return true;
17317 }
17318 return false;
17319 }
17320
17322 bool LoadNext() override
17323 {
17324 /* Since there can be holes in the staff style "chain", there
17325 need to be a better method to find items. Scanning a gap of 20 items
17326 should be an ok workaround for most documents. */
17327 int itemno = GetItemNo();
17328 for (int i = 1; i <= 20; i++)
17329 {
17330 if (Load(itemno + i)) return true;
17331 }
17332 return false;
17333 }
17334
17335#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
17336protected:
17337#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
17338
17339 EXTAG Tag() override { return ot_EDTStaffStyle2010; }
17340 int DataSizeLoad() override
17341 {
17342 switch (_VersionToUse())
17343 {
17344 case FINALEVERSION_2014:
17345 return sizeof(EDTStaffStyle2014);
17346 case FINALEVERSION_2012:
17347 return sizeof(EDTStaffStyle2012);
17348 default:
17349 return sizeof(EDTStaffStyle2010);
17350 }
17351 }
17352 void* Allocate() override
17353 {
17354 switch (_VersionToUse())
17355 {
17356 case FINALEVERSION_2014:
17357 return (void*) &_staffstyledef2014;
17358 case FINALEVERSION_2012:
17359 return (void*) &_staffstyledef2012;
17360 default:
17361 return (void*) &_staffstyledef2010;
17362 }
17363 }
17364 EVERSION EnigmaVersion() override { return _VersionToUse(); }

18141

18143 { return new FCStaffStyleAssign(); }
18144
18145#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
18146public:

18149
18150#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
18157 void* _GetStaffStyleAssign() { return Allocate(); }
18158#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
18159
18164 FCStaffStyleAssign() : __FCInciOther()
18165 {
18166 memset(&_staffstyleassign, 0, sizeof(_staffstyleassign));
18167 _datablock = &_staffstyleassign;
18168 _loadedsize = sizeof(_staffstyleassign);

18198

18204
18209 void SetStartMeasure(eMeas value) { _staffstyleassign.range.start.meas = value; }
18210
18215 void SetStartMeasurePos(TimeEdu32 value) { _staffstyleassign.range.start.edu = value; }
18216
18221 void SetEndMeasure(eMeas value) { _staffstyleassign.range.end.meas = value; }
18222
18227 void SetEndMeasurePos(TimeEdu32 value) { _staffstyleassign.range.end.edu = value; }
18228
18233 void SetStyleID(twobyte value) { _staffstyleassign.style = value; }
18234
18239 eStaff GetStaff() const override { return _dataid.other.cmper; };
18240
18246 void SetEndMeasurePosRight() { SetEndMeasurePos(0x7fffffff); }
18247
18252 bool IsOverlapping(FCMusicRegion* pRegion)
18253 {
18254 if (!pRegion) return false;
18255 if (GetEndMeasure() < pRegion->GetStartMeasure()) return false;
18256 if (GetStartMeasure() > pRegion->GetEndMeasure()) return false;
18257 if (GetEndMeasure() == pRegion->GetStartMeasure())
18258 {
18259 if (GetEndMeasurePos() < pRegion->GetStartMeasurePos()) return false;
18260 }
18261 if (GetStartMeasure() == pRegion->GetEndMeasure())
18262 {
18263 if (GetStartMeasurePos() > pRegion->GetEndMeasurePos()) return false;
18264 }
18265 // Horizontally, it's an overlap - check the staff:
18266 if (pRegion->IsStaffIncluded(GetStaff())) return true;
18267 return false;
18268 }
18269
18270#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DEBUG
18271 void DebugDump() override
18272 {
18273 __FCInciOther::DebugDump();
18274 DebugOutInt("Style ID: ", GetStyleID());
18275 DebugOutInt("Start measure: ", GetStartMeasure());
18276 DebugOutInt("End measure: ", GetEndMeasure());
18277 }
18278#endif
18279};

18665 {
18666 if (staffno == 0) return false;
18667 if (staffno == GetFirstStaff()) return true;
18668 if (staffno == GetSecondStaff()) return true;
18669 if (staffno == GetThirdStaff()) return true;
18670 return false;
18671 }
18672
18677 CMPER GetFirstStaff() const { return _multistaffinstgroup.staffNum1; }
18678

18727 _multistaffinstgroup.staffGroupID = value;

18730
18737 CMPER CalcTopStaff()
18738 {
18739 CMPER returnvalue = 0;
18740 twobyte lowestslot = 10000;
18741 twobyte slottest = FX_InstToSlot(GetFirstStaff(), 0);
18742 if (slottest)
18743 {
18744 lowestslot = slottest;
18745 returnvalue = GetFirstStaff();
18746 }
18747 slottest = FX_InstToSlot(GetSecondStaff(), 0);
18748 if ((slottest) && (slottest < lowestslot))
18749 {
18750 lowestslot = slottest;
18751 returnvalue = GetSecondStaff();
18752 }
18753 slottest = FX_InstToSlot(GetThirdStaff(), 0);
18754 if ((slottest) && (slottest < lowestslot))
18755 {
18756 returnvalue = GetThirdStaff();
18757 }
18758 return returnvalue;
18759 }
18760
18767 CMPER CalcBottomStaff()
18768 {
18769 CMPER returnvalue = 0;
18770 twobyte highestslot = -10000;
18771 twobyte slottest = FX_InstToSlot(GetFirstStaff(), 0);
18772 if (slottest)
18773 {
18774 highestslot = slottest;
18775 returnvalue = GetFirstStaff();
18776 }
18777 slottest = FX_InstToSlot(GetSecondStaff(), 0);
18778 if ((slottest) && (slottest > highestslot))
18779 {
18780 highestslot = slottest;
18781 returnvalue = GetSecondStaff();
18782 }
18783 slottest = FX_InstToSlot(GetThirdStaff(), 0);
18784 if ((slottest) && (slottest > highestslot))
18785 {
18786 returnvalue = GetThirdStaff();
18787 }
18788 return returnvalue;
18789 }
18790
18791
18792#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DEBUG
18793 void DebugDump() override
18794 {
18795 __FCNoInciOther::DebugDump();
18796 DebugOutInt("First staff: ", GetFirstStaff());
18797 DebugOutInt("Second staff: ", GetSecondStaff());
18798 DebugOutInt("Third staff: ", GetThirdStaff());
18799 DebugOutInt("Group ID: ", GetGroupID());
18800 }
18801#endif
18802};

18836 _loadedsize = sizeof(_allotment);
18837 }
18838
18839 __FCBaseData* CreateObject() override { return new FCAllotment(); }
18840
18841
18842 bool LoadFirst() override
18843 {
18844 CMPER trycmper = 0; // 0 is used for default allotment
18845 while (!Load(trycmper))
18846 {
18847 if (trycmper > 8192) return false;
18848 trycmper ++;
18849 }
18850 return true;
18851 }
18852
18853 bool LoadNext() override
18854 {
18855 CMPER trycmper = GetItemNo() + 1;
18856 while (!Load(trycmper))
18857 {
18858 if (trycmper > 8192) return false;
18859 trycmper ++;
18860 }
18861 return true;
18862 }
18863
18864
18865#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
18866public:
18867 const char* ClassName() override { return "FCAllotment"; }
18868 const PDKFRAMEWORK_CLASSID GetClassID() const override { return FCID_ALLOTMENT; }
18869
18870#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
18877 void* _GetAllotment() { return Allocate(); }
18878#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
18879
18881 FCAllotment() : __FCNoInciOther()
18882 {
18883 memset(&_allotment, 0, sizeof(_allotment));
18884 _datablock = &_allotment;
18885 _loadedsize = sizeof(_allotment);
18886 }
18887
18889 void SetWidth(twobyte width)
18890 {
18891 _allotment.allotment = width;
18892 }
18893
18894
18896 twobyte GetWidth()
18897 {
18898 return _allotment.allotment;
18899 }
18900

18902#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DEBUG
18903 void DebugDump() override
18904 {
18905 __FCNoInciOther::DebugDump();
18906 DebugOutInt("Allotment Width: ", GetWidth());
18907 }

19274
19279 void SetIndependentRightPage(bool state)
19280 {
19281 if (GetIndependentRightPage() == state) return;
19282 /* Copy the alignment */
19283 if (state)
19284 _graphic.rightPgAlignFlags = _graphic.alignFlags;
19285 else
19286 _graphic.rightPgAlignFlags = 0;
19287 }

19304 _graphic.rightPgBottom = value;
19305 }
19306
19312 void SetFixedPercent(bool state) { Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_FIXEDPERC, state); }
19313
19323 void SetHorizontalAlignment(
19324#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
19325 GRAPHIC_HORIZONTAL_ALIGN
19326#else
19327 FLAG_16
19328#endif
19329 alignment
19330 )
19331 {
19332 switch (alignment)
19333 {
19334 case GRAPHICHORIZALIGN_LEFT:
19335 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_LEFT, true);
19336 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_RIGHT, false);
19337 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERH, false);
19338 break;
19339 case GRAPHICHORIZALIGN_RIGHT:
19340 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_LEFT, false);
19341 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_RIGHT, true);
19342 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERH, false);
19343 break;
19344 default: /* Horizontally centered */
19345 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_LEFT, false);
19346 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_RIGHT, false);
19347 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERH, true);
19348 break;
19349 }
19350 if (!GetIndependentRightPage()) SetHorizontalAlignmentRightPage(alignment);
19351 }
19352
19359 void SetHorizontalAlignmentRightPage(
19360#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
19361 GRAPHIC_HORIZONTAL_ALIGN
19362#else
19363 FLAG_16
19364#endif
19365 alignment)
19366 {
19367 switch (alignment)
19368 {
19369 case GRAPHICHORIZALIGN_LEFT:
19370 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_LEFT, true);
19371 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_RIGHT, false);
19372 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERH, false);
19373 break;
19374 case GRAPHICHORIZALIGN_RIGHT:
19375 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_LEFT, false);
19376 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_RIGHT, true);
19377 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERH, false);
19378 break;
19379 default: /* Horizontally centered */
19380 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_LEFT, false);
19381 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_RIGHT, false);
19382 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERH, true);
19383 break;
19384 }
19385 }
19386
19392 void SetVerticalAlignment(
19393#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
19394 GRAPHIC_VERTICAL_ALIGN
19395#else
19396 int
19397#endif
19398 alignment
19399 )
19400 {
19401 /* If GetIndependentRightPage() is ON, copy the vertical alignment
19402 * there as well (to make sure they are in synch). */
19403 switch (alignment)
19404 {
19405 case GRAPHICVERTALIGN_TOP:
19406 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_TOP, true);
19407 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_BOTTOM, false);
19408 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERV, false);
19409 if (GetIndependentRightPage())
19410 {
19411 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_TOP, true);
19412 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_BOTTOM, false);
19413 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERV, false);
19414 }
19415 break;
19416 case GRAPHICVERTALIGN_BOTTOM:
19417 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_TOP, false);
19418 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_BOTTOM, true);
19419 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERV, false);
19420 if (GetIndependentRightPage())
19421 {
19422 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_TOP, false);
19423 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_BOTTOM, true);
19424 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERV, false);
19425 }
19426 break;
19427 default:
19428 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_TOP, false);
19429 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_BOTTOM, false);
19430 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.alignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERV, true);
19431 if (GetIndependentRightPage())
19432 {
19433 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_TOP, false);
19434 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_BOTTOM, false);
19435 Set16BitFlag(&_graphic.rightPgAlignFlags, GRAPHIC_ALIGN_CENTERV, true);
19436 }
19437 break;
19438 }
19439 }
19440};

20500/* MAKEEXTAG(edOther, 'f','t') doesn't work correctly. */
20501
20502const EXTAG __ot_FRETSTYLE = MAKEEXTAG(MAKETAG(edMultiInciOther,13), 'f','t');
20503
20504const int __MAX_FRET_NAME_LEN = 47; // Max number of characters of names of
20505const int __MAX_FRET_NUM_TEXT_LEN = 23;
20506
20507#include "pragma_align_begin.h"
20508struct __FCFretStyle // ot_FRETSTYLE (1 logical incidences, 14 physical incidences (0..13))
20509 // cmper comes from EDTChord2010::fbStyleID
20510{
20511 // start of physical incident 0 (0 based)
20512 tbool showLastFret; // Show the last fret when drawing fretboards
20513 tbool rotate; // Rotate the diagram so the nut is on the left
20514 tbool fingNumWhite; // Draw fingering numbers white.
20515
20516 // CMPERs of the various shapes that can be drawn on the fretboard diagram. When these
20517 // are zero, the hardcoded shapes will be used. (Hardcoded shapes are designed to look
20518 // like the Seville Font.)
20519
20520 eShape fingStrShapeID; // ID of ot_SHAPEDEF record used for drawing
20521 // a fingered (closed) string shape
20522 eShape openStrShapeID; // ID of ot_SHAPEDEF record used for drawing
20523 // an open string shape
20524 eShape muteStrShapeID; // ID of ot_SHAPEDEF record used for drawing
20525 // a muted string shape
20526 // start of physical incident 1 (0 based)
20527 eShape barreShapeID; // ID of ot_SHAPEDEF record used for drawing
20528 // the fretboard barre shape
20529 eShape customShapeID; // ID of the ot_SHAPEDEF record used for
20530 // drawing the user defined shape
20531 utwobyte defNumFrets; // The number of frets to show by default in this style
20532
20533 // Following are the high and low twobyte fields that, together, designate various
20534 // Efix32 values for the fretboard style.
20535
20536 twobyte stringGapHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20537 twobyte stringGapLo; // Efix32 string gap (right edge to right edge)
20538
20539 twobyte fretGapHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20540 // start of physical incident 2 (0 based)
20541 twobyte fretGapLo; // Efix32 fret gap (bottom edge to bottom edge)
20542
20543 twobyte stringWidthHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20544 twobyte stringWidthLo; // Efix32 width of strings
20545
20546 twobyte fretWidthHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20547 twobyte fretWidthLo; // Efix32 width of frets
20548
20549 twobyte nutWidthHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20550 // start of physical incident 3 (0 based)
20551 twobyte nutWidthLo; // Efix32 width of the nut
20552
20553 twobyte vertTextOffHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20554 twobyte vertTextOffLo; // Efix32 vert offset of fret number text
20555
20556 twobyte horzTextOffHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20557 twobyte horzTextOffLo; // Efix32 horz offset of fret number text
20558
20559 twobyte horzHandleOffHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20560 // start of physical incident 4 (0 based)
20561 twobyte horzHandleOffLo; // Efix32 horz offset of the fretboard's handle
20562
20563 twobyte vertHandleOffHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20564 twobyte vertHandleOffLo; // Efix32 vert offset of the fretboard's handle
20565
20566 twobyte whiteoutHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20567 twobyte whiteoutLo; // Efix32 whiteout of strings for fingering numbers
20568
20569 // Font information
20570
20571 EFONTID fretNumFontID; // Font ID, size and EFX data for the
20572 // start of physical incident 5 (0 based)
20573 FontPoints16 fretNumFontSize; // fret number font. (Designates which
20574 FLAG_16 fretNumFontEfx; // fret is the first shown in the diagram
20575
20576 EFONTID fingNumFontID; // Font ID, size and EFX data for the
20577 FontPoints16 fingNumFontSize; // fingering numbers font used in the.
20578 FLAG_16 fingNumFontEfx; // fretboard diagrams
20579
20580 // Fingering number offsets
20581 twobyte horzFingNumOffHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20582 // start of physical incident 6 (0 based)
20583 twobyte horzFingNumOffLo; // Efix32 horizontal finger number offset
20584
20585 twobyte vertFingNumOffHi; // High and low twobyte values for
20586 twobyte vertFingNumOffLo; // Efix32 vertical finger number offset
20587
20588 twobyte pad[3]; // Unused--padding to make size mult of OTSIZE
20589
20590 // start of physical incident 7 (0 based)
20591 ECHAR name[__MAX_FRET_NAME_LEN + 1]; // The name of the fretboard style
20592
20593 ECHAR fretNumText[__MAX_FRET_NUM_TEXT_LEN + 1];
20594 // The text to display after the
20595 // fret number (e.g., 'fr' or 'fret')
20596 // end of physical incident 13 (0 based)
20597};
20598#include "pragma_align_end.h"
20599
20600#endif /* #ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */

21987 void SetTargetTrigger(
21988#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
21989FCTextRepeat::REPTARGETTRIGGERS
21990#else
21991int
21992#endif
21993 value
21994 )
21995 {
21996 switch (value)

21998 case FCTextRepeat::REPTARGET_MEASURENUM:
21999 _backwardrepeat.flag &= ~BackRepeat_ACTION_BITS;
22000 _backwardrepeat.flag |= 0x10;
22001 break;
22002 case FCTextRepeat::REPTARGET_FORWARDS:
22003 _backwardrepeat.flag &= ~BackRepeat_ACTION_BITS;
22004 _backwardrepeat.flag |= 0x20;
22005 break;
22006 case FCTextRepeat::REPTARGET_NEXTENDING:
22007 _backwardrepeat.flag &= ~BackRepeat_ACTION_BITS;
22008 break;
22009 case FCTextRepeat::REPTARGET_UNDEFINED:
22010 case FCTextRepeat::REPTARGET_DEFID:

22013 break;

22023 Set16BitFlag(&_backwardrepeat.flag, BackRepeat_CLRonCHANGE, state);
22024 }
22025
22034#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
22035 FCTextRepeat::REPACTIONS
22036#else
22037 int
22038#endif
22039 GetAction() const
22040 {
22041 switch (_backwardrepeat.flag & 0xc00)
22042 {
22043 case 0x00:
22044 return FCTextRepeat::REPACTION_ALWAYSJUMP;
22045 case 0x400:
22046 return FCTextRepeat::REPACTION_JUMPONPASS;
22047 case 0x800:
22048 return FCTextRepeat::REPACTION_PLAYSECTION;
22049 default:
22050 break;
22051 }
22052
22053#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DEBUG
22054 DebugOutHex("Undefined flag state for FCBackwardRepeat:GetAction: ", _backwardrepeat.flag);
22055#endif
22056 return FCTextRepeat::REPACTION_ALWAYSJUMP;
22057 }
22058
22067 void SetAction(
22068#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
22069 FCTextRepeat::REPACTIONS
22070#else
22071 int
22072#endif
22073 mode)
22074 {
22075 switch (mode)
22076 {
22077 case FCTextRepeat::REPACTION_ALWAYSJUMP:
22078 /* 0x0c40 bits should all be off */
22079 Set16BitFlag(&_backwardrepeat.flag, 0x0c00, false);
22080 break;
22081
22082 case FCTextRepeat::REPACTION_JUMPONPASS:
22083 /* 0x0400 (in the 0x0c40 bit set) represents the "jump on pass" */
22084 Set16BitFlag(&_backwardrepeat.flag, 0x0c00, false);
22085 Set16BitFlag(&_backwardrepeat.flag, 0x0400, true);
22086 break;
22087
22088 case FCTextRepeat::REPACTION_PLAYSECTION:
22089 /* 0x0800 (in the 0x0c40 bit set) represents the "play section" */
22090 Set16BitFlag(&_backwardrepeat.flag, 0x0c00, false);
22091 Set16BitFlag(&_backwardrepeat.flag, 0x0800, true);
22092 break;
22093
22094 case FCTextRepeat::REPACTION_NEVERJUMP:
22095 case FCTextRepeat::REPACTION_STOPONPASS:
22096 break;
22097 }
22098 }
22099
22112 FCSeparatePlacements* CreateSeparatePlacements();
22113
22114#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY_CPP
22116 luabridge::RefCountedPtr<FCSeparatePlacements> CreateSeparatePlacements_GC()
22117 { return CreateSeparatePlacements(); }
22118#endif
22119

22403class FCTempoElement : public __FCInciOther
22404{
22405private:
22406#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
22410 EDTTempo _tempo;
22411
22412protected:
22413 EXTAG Tag() override { return ot_Tempo; }
22414 int DataSizeLoad() override { return sizeof(EDTTempo); }
22415 void* Allocate() override { return (void*) &_tempo; }
22416
22421 void CloneMemoryFrom(__FCBaseData* pSource) override
22422 {
22423 memcpy(&_tempo, ((FCTempoElement*)pSource)->_GetTempoElement(), sizeof(_tempo));
22424 _datablock = &_tempo;
22425 _loadedsize = sizeof(_tempo);
22426 }
22427
22428 __FCBaseData* CreateObject() override { return new FCTempoElement(); }
22429#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
22430public:
22431
22432 const char* ClassName() override { return "FCTempoElement"; }
22433 const PDKFRAMEWORK_CLASSID GetClassID() const override { return FCID_TEMPOELEMENT; }
22434
22435#ifndef DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS
22442 void* _GetTempoElement() { return &_tempo; }
22443#endif /* DOXYGEN_SHOULD_IGNORE_THIS */
22444
22449 FCTempoElement() : __FCInciOther()
22450 {
22451 memset(&_tempo, 0, sizeof(_tempo));
22452 _tempo.unit = 1000;
22453 _datablock = &_tempo;
22454 _loadedsize = sizeof(_tempo);
22455 }
22456
22461 void SetMeasurePos(twobyte edupos) { _tempo.eldur = edupos; }
22462
22467 TimeEdu32 GetMeasurePos() const override { return _tempo.eldur; }
22468
22474 bool GetAbsolute() const { return _tempo.flag == TIMEDIAL_ABSOLUTE; }
22475
22482 void SetAbsolute(bool value)
22483 {
22484 _tempo.flag = value ? TIMEDIAL_ABSOLUTE : TIMEDIAL_RELATIVE;
22485 }
22486
22492 fourbyte GetRatio() const { return _tempo.ratio; }
22493
22498 void SetRatio(fourbyte value) { _tempo.ratio = value; }
22499
22509 float CalcValue()
22510 {
22511 if (GetAbsolute())
22512 {
22513 float result = _tempo.ratio * _tempo.unit;
22514 result /= 65536;
22515 /* The value here is relative to 60 BPM == 1024 */
22516 result *= 60;
22517 result /= 1024;
22518 /* Round it off to 2 decimals */
22519 fourbyte fb = (fourbyte) (result * 100);
22520 result = fb;
22521 result /= 100;
22522 return result;
22523 }
22524 else
22525 {
22526 /* Relative */
22527 float result = GetRatio();
22528 result /= 10;
22529 return result;
22530 }
22531 }
22532
22539 void SetAbsoluteValue(float value)
22540 {
22541 SetAbsolute(true);
22542 _tempo.unit = 1000;
22543 value *= 1024;
22544 value /= 60;
22545 value *= 65536;
22546 value /= 1000;
22547 _tempo.ratio = (fourbyte) value;
22548 }
22549
22556 void SetRelativeValue(float value)
22557 {
22558 SetAbsolute(false);
22559 SetRatio((fourbyte) (value * 10));
22560 }
22561};

22565#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_TINYXML

23000class FCLayerPlaybackData : public __FCBase
23001{
23002 __EDTLayerPlayData* _pLayerData;
23003public:
23008 FCLayerPlaybackData(__EDTLayerPlayData* pData) : __FCBase()
23009 {
23010 _pLayerData = pData;
23011 }
23012 const char* ClassName() override { return "FCLayerPlaybackData"; }
23013
23018 ePlaybackRoute GetInstrumentDefID() const
23019 {
23020 /* The value is 0-based!!! To be able to map to FCInstrumentDef, it
23021 * needs to be 1-based. */
23022 return _pLayerData->playbackRouteNum + 1;
23023 }
23024
23029 bool GetPlay() const
23030 {
23031 return GetBitFlag(_pLayerData->playFlags, __PLAY_LAYER_TRACK);
23032 }
23033
23038 bool GetSolo() const
23039 {
23040 return GetBitFlag(_pLayerData->playFlags, __SOLO_LAYER_TRACK);
23041 }
23042
23049 void SetInstrumentDefID(ePlaybackRoute value)
23050 {
23051 /* The value is 0-based!!! (To be able to map to FCInstrumentDef, it
23052 * needs to be 1-based.) */
23053 _pLayerData->playbackRouteNum = value - 1;
23054 }
23055
23060 void SetPlay(bool state)
23061 {
23062 return Set16BitFlag(&_pLayerData->playFlags, __PLAY_LAYER_TRACK, state);
23063 }
23064
23069 void SetSolo(bool state)
23070 {
23071 return Set16BitFlag(&_pLayerData->playFlags, __SOLO_LAYER_TRACK, state);
23072 }
23073};

23105 _datablock = &_playbackdata;

23158 FCLayerPlaybackData* GetChordLayerData()
23159 {
23160 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return NULL;
23161 if (_pChordLayer) return _pChordLayer;
23162 _pChordLayer = new FCLayerPlaybackData(&_playbackdata.chordPlayData);
23163 return _pChordLayer;
23164 }
23165
23178 FCLayerPlaybackData* GetMidiExpressionLayerData()
23179 {
23180 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return NULL;
23181 if (_pExpressionLayer) return _pExpressionLayer;
23182 _pExpressionLayer = new FCLayerPlaybackData(&_playbackdata.MIDIExpressionsPlayData);
23183 return _pExpressionLayer;
23184 }
23185
23186
23201 FCLayerPlaybackData* GetNoteLayerData(int layernumber)
23202 {
23203 if ((layernumber < 1) || (layernumber > 4)) return NULL;
23204 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return NULL;
23205 layernumber--; /* Make a 0-based index */
23206 if (_pNoteLayers[layernumber]) return _pNoteLayers[layernumber];
23207 _pNoteLayers[layernumber] = new FCLayerPlaybackData(&_playbackdata.layerPlayData[layernumber]);
23208 return _pNoteLayers[layernumber];
23209 }

23523
23543 void SetMode(
23544#ifndef PDK_FRAMEWORK_LUAFRIENDLY
23545 STAFFLIST_MODES
23546#else
23547 int
23548#endif
23549 mode
23550 )
23551 {
23552 switch (mode)
23553 {
23554 case SLMODE_SCORE:
23555 SetCustomTag(ot_StaffListDataScore);
23556 break;
23557 case SLMODE_PARTS:
23558 SetCustomTag(ot_StaffListDataParts);
23559 break;
23560 case SLMODE_FORCESCORE:
23561 SetCustomTag(ot_StaffListForceScore);
23562 break;
23563 case SLMODE_FORCEPARTS:
23564 SetCustomTag(ot_StaffListForceParts);
23565 break;
23566
23567 case SLMODE_CATEGORY_SCORE:
23568 SetCustomTag(__ot_CategoryStaffListScore);
23569 break;
23570 case SLMODE_CATEGORY_PARTS:
23571 SetCustomTag(__ot_CategoryStaffListParts);
23572 break;
23573 case SLMODE_CATEGORY_FORCESCORE:
23574 SetCustomTag(__ot_CategoryStaffListScoreOverride);
23575 break;
23576 case SLMODE_CATEGORY_FORCEPARTS:
23577 SetCustomTag(__ot_CategoryStaffListPartsOverride);
23578 break;
23579
23580 case SLMODE_ASSIGNMENT_SCORE:
23581 SetCustomTag(__ot_StaffAssignStaffListScore);
23582 break;
23583 case SLMODE_ASSIGNMENT_PARTS:
23584 SetCustomTag(__ot_StaffAssignStaffListParts);
23585 break;
23586 case SLMODE_ASSIGNMENT_FORCESCORE:
23587 SetCustomTag(__ot_StaffAssignStaffListScoreOverride);
23588 break;
23589 case SLMODE_ASSIGNMENT_FORCEPARTS:
23590 SetCustomTag(__ot_StaffAssignStaffListPartsOverride);
23591 break;
23592 }
23593 }

23616
23622 int GetElementCount() const
23623 {
23624 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return 0;
23625 int maxcount = _loadedsize / sizeof(EDTStaffList);
23626 /* Reduce list if some elements are 0 at the end */
23627 while (maxcount > 0)
23628 {
23629 if (_TypeCast()[maxcount - 1].staff == 0)
23630 maxcount --;
23631 else
23632 return maxcount;
23633 }
23634 return maxcount;
23635 }
23636
23642 int GetStaffCount() const
23643 {
23644 if (!DataIsLoaded()) return 0;
23645 int maxcount = _loadedsize / sizeof(EDTStaffList);
23646 int staffcount = 0;
23647 for (int i = 0; i < maxcount; i++)
23648 {
23649 if (_TypeCast()[i].staff > 0) staffcount++;
23650 }
23651 return staffcount;
23652 }
23653
23663 int GetStaff(int index)
23664 {
23665 if (index < 0) return 0;
23666 int maxcount = _loadedsize / sizeof(EDTStaffList);
23667 int staffcount = 0;
23668 for (int i = 0; i < maxcount; i++)
23669 {
23670 if (_TypeCast()[i].staff > 0)
23671 {
23672 if (staffcount == index) return _TypeCast()[index].staff;
23673 staffcount++;
23674 }
23675 }
23676 return 0;
23677 }
23678
23683 bool IsElementAvailable(twobyte stafflistelement)
23684 {
23685 if (stafflistelement == 0) return false; /* This value would not be a valid value in a staff list. */
23686 int maxcount = _loadedsize / sizeof(EDTStaffList);
23687 for (int i = 0; i < maxcount; i++)
23688 {
23689 if (_TypeCast()[i].staff == stafflistelement) return true;
23690 }
23691 return false;
23692 }
23693
23698 bool IncludesTopStaff()
23699 {
23700 return IsElementAvailable(SLD_TOPSTAFF);
23701 }
23702
23707 bool IncludesBottomStaff()
23708 {
23709 return IsElementAvailable(SLD_BOTTOMSTAFF);
23710 }
23711
23718 bool IncludesStaff(twobyte staffnumber)
23719 {
23720 return IsElementAvailable(staffnumber);
23721 }

24047 bool GetName(FCString* pString)
24048 {
24049 if (!pString) return false;
24050 if (_Use25_3Version())
24051 {
24052 /* Unicode version */
24053 FIN25_3_CODE( pString->SetUnicodeString((eUniChar16*) _GetNamePtr()); )
24054 }
24055 else
24056 {
24057 /* Old ECHAR version */
24058 pString->SetCString((ECHAR*) _GetNamePtr());
24059 }
24060
24061 return true;

24063
24074 bool SetName(FCString* pString)
24075 {
24076 if (!pString) return false;
24077 if (pString->GetLength() > 47) return false;
24078 if (_Use25_3Version())
24079 {
24080 /* Unicode version */
24081 FIN25_3_CODE( pString->CopyToUnicodeBuffer((eUniChar16*) _GetNamePtr()); )
24082 }
24083 else
24084 {
24085 /* Old ECHAR version */
24086 strcpy((ECHAR*) _GetNamePtr(), pString->GetCString());
24087 }
24088 return true;
24089 }
24090
24101 twobyte GetStringTuning(int stringnumber)
24102 {
24103 if (stringnumber < 1) return 0;
24104 if (stringnumber > GetStringCount()) return 0;
24105 if (stringnumber > 24) return 0;
24106
24107 /* The meaning of the StringTuning array has shifted a bit between PDKs.
24108 */
24109#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_25_3
24110 if (_Use25_3Version())
24111 {
24112 return ((EDTStringData*)_GetStringTuningPtr(stringnumber))->pitch;
24113 }
24114#endif
24115 return *(twobyte*)_GetStringTuningPtr(stringnumber);
24116 }
24117
24129 bool SetStringTuning(int stringnumber, twobyte midinumber)
24130 {
24131 if (stringnumber < 1) return false;
24132 if (stringnumber > GetStringCount()) return false;
24133 if (stringnumber > 24) return false;
24134
24135 if (_Use25_3Version())
24136 {
24137#if FXT_VERSION >= FINALEVERSION_25_3
24138 ((EDTStringData*)_GetStringTuningPtr(stringnumber))->pitch = midinumber;
24139#endif
24140 }
24141 else
24142 {
24143 *(twobyte*)_GetStringTuningPtr(stringnumber) = midinumber;
24144 }
24145 return true;
24146 }
24147
24152 bool IsDiatonic()
24153 {
24154 return (MAKELONG(*_GetDiatonicStepsLoPtr(), *_GetDiatonicStepsHiPtr()) != 0);
24155 }
24156
24161 int GetDiatonicCount()
24162 {
24163 if (!IsDiatonic()) return 0;
24164 ufourbyte fb = MAKELONG(*_GetDiatonicStepsLoPtr(), *_GetDiatonicStepsHiPtr());
24165 int totalcount = 0;
24166 while (fb)
24167 {
24168 if (fb & 0x01) totalcount ++;
24169 fb = fb >> 1;
24170 }
24171 return totalcount;
24172 }
24173
24181 bool GetDiatonicInfo(FCNumbers* pNumbers)
24182 {
24183 if (!pNumbers) return false;
24184 pNumbers->ClearAll();
24185 ufourbyte fb = MAKELONG(*_GetDiatonicStepsLoPtr(), *_GetDiatonicStepsHiPtr());
24186 int count = 0;
24187 while (fb != 0)
24188 {
24189 count ++;
24190 if (fb & 0x01)
24191 {
24192 pNumbers->Add(new FCNumber(count));
24193 count = 0;
24194 }
24195 fb = fb >> 1;
24196 }
24197 return true;
24198 }
24199
24207 bool SetDiatonicInfo(FCNumbers* pNumbers)
24208 {
24209 if (!pNumbers) return false;
24210 ufourbyte fb = 0;
24211 for (int i = pNumbers->GetCount() - 1; i >= 0; i--)
24212 {
24213 FCNumber* pNumber = pNumbers->GetItemAt(i);
24214 if (pNumber->GetInt() < 1) return false;
24215 if (pNumber->GetInt() > 5) return false;
24216 fb = fb << 1; /* Shift to next number */
24217 fb |= 0x01;
24218 for (int bitcount = 0; bitcount < pNumber->GetInt() - 1; bitcount++)
24219 {
24220 fb = fb << 1; /* Shift with extra zeros, if necessary */
24221 }
24222 }
24223 *(utwobyte*)_GetDiatonicStepsLoPtr() = LOWORD(fb);
24224 *(utwobyte*)_GetDiatonicStepsHiPtr() = HIWORD(fb);
24225 return true;
24226 }
24227
24228
24229#ifdef PDK_FRAMEWORK_DEBUG
24230 void DebugDump() override
24231 {
24232 __FCNoInciOther::DebugDump();
24233 DebugOutHex("Diatonic bit set: ", MAKELONG(*_GetDiatonicStepsLoPtr(), *_GetDiatonicStepsHiPtr()));
24234 }
24235#endif
24236};
